Class Erststimme

  • java.lang.Object
    • Erststimme

  • public class Erststimme
extends java.lang.Object
    accesses remote json data at abgeordnetenwatch.de or local for retrieving information about the candidates of a parliament. If local, the parliament data is all contained in src/resources/parliament2profile.json. If remote, the json file is mapped after creating the url. For creating the url the parliamentName is necessary. It is possible to call() the Erststimme to receive a string of an answer to a political category for Alexa output. Common category have a common top level Group. Mapping is done via class Themen, which has a GroupMapping attribute. A question includes answer and category according to json profile of abgeordnetenwatch.de. A Klient instance is created with a category and used with a url for retrieving the answer to a question concerning this category.
    Version:
    1.1, 13.10.2017
    Author:
    Rainer Wichmann, Severin Engelmann

        Parameters:
